File truncated. Reading remainder:## Full Rendering Logic of `plan-panel.ts`

### File Overview
Single file (~380 lines). Orchestrator plan status widget — flat text, no box borders. Uses `ctx.ui.setWidget()` to sit above editor.

---

### Key Code: `renderPlanLines()` (the core renderer)

```ts
function renderPlanLines(): string[] {
    if (!planState) return [];
    const { goal, steps, startTime } = planState;
    const elapsed = Date.now() - startTime;
    const elapsedStr = formatDuration(elapsed).padStart(6);
    const total = steps.length;
    const completedCount = steps.filter((s) => s.completed).length;
    const erroredCount = steps.filter((s) => s.errored).length;
    const goalTrunc = goal.length > 55 ? goal.slice(0, 52) + "..." : goal;

    // Header: Plan ◆ <goal>  ● N/N  duration
    const prog = erroredCount > 0
        ? `● ${completedCount}/${total} ✗${erroredCount}`
        : `● ${completedCount}/${total}`;
    const lines: string[] = [`Plan: ◆ ${goalTrunc}  ${prog}  ${elapsedStr}`];

    const BUDGET = 9; // hard cap 10 lines, header uses 1
    const frames = SPINNER_FRAMES; // ["⠋","⠙","⠹","⠸","⠼","⠴","⠦","⠧","⠇","⠏"]
    const idx = _spinnerIndex % frames.length;

    // Build rows in CHRONOLOGICAL order
    const rows = [];
    for (const s of steps) {
        if (s.errored)       rows.push({ icon: "✗",        label: s.label });
        else if (s.completed) rows.push({ icon: "✓",       label: s.label });
        else if (s.active)    rows.push({
            icon: frames[idx], // animated spinner
            label: s.label,
            detail: s.detailLines?.length ? undefined : s.detail,
            detailLines: s.detailLines,
        });
        else                  rows.push({ icon: "○",       label: s.label });
    }

    // Fit check: if all rows + detail lines fit within BUDGET, render all
    const lineCounts = rows.map((r) => 1 + (r.detailLines?.length ?? 0));
    const totalDisplayLines = lineCounts.reduce((a, b) => a + b, 0);

    if (totalDisplayLines <= BUDGET) {
        for (const r of rows) _renderPlanRow(lines, r);
    } else {
        // Trim oldest rows (top) to fit; keep newest (bottom)
        let budget = BUDGET;
        const kept = [];
        for (let i = rows.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
            const needed = lineCounts[i];
            if (needed <= budget) { kept.unshift(rows[i]); budget -= needed; }
            else if (budget >= 1) { kept.unshift({ icon: rows[i].icon, label: rows[i].label }); budget = 0; }
        }
        const hidden = rows.length - kept.length;
        if (hidden > 0) lines.push(`  … +${hidden} more`);
        for (const r of kept) _renderPlanRow(lines, r);
    }
    return lines;
}
```

### Key Code: `_renderPlanRow()` (single step renderer)

```ts
function _renderPlanRow(lines, r) {
    if (r.detailLines && r.detailLines.length > 0) {
        lines.push(`  → ${r.label}`);        // arrow for substep header
        for (const dl of r.detailLines) lines.push(dl); // indented detail lines
    } else {
        const suffix = r.detail ? ` — ${r.detail}` : "";
        lines.push(`  ${r.icon} ${r.label}${suffix}`);
    }
}
```

---

### Icons/Spacing Summary

| State | Icon | Format |
|-------|------|--------|
| Completed | `✓` | `  ✓ <label>` |
| Errored | `✗` | `  ✗ <label>` |
| Active | `⠋`..`⠏` (spinning) | `  ⠋ <label> — <detail>` or `  → <label>` + detail lines |
| Pending | `○` | `  ○ <label>` |
| Truncated | — | `  … +N more` |
| Header | `◆` | `Plan: ◆ <goal>  ● N/N  <duration>` |

All rows prefixed with 2-space indent. Em-dash `—` separates label from detail. Arrow `→` used when `detailLines` array present (replaces icon).

---

### Widget Setup

```ts
export function setupPlanPanel(goal, stepLabels, ctx) {
    planState = { goal, steps: stepLabels.map((label, i) => ({
        label, completed: false, errored: false, active: i === 0,
    })), startTime: Date.now() };
    _setWidget = ctx.ui.setWidget.bind(ctx.ui);
    _lastWidgetContent = null;
    startPlanTimer();  // 80ms spinner + 1s elapsed
    _renderWidget();
}
```

Two timers: **spinner** (80ms, smooth animation) + **elapsed** (1s, clock update). Both call `_renderWidget()` which skips push if content identical to last (cache check).

---

### Public State Mutators

| Function | Effect |
|----------|--------|
| `setupPlanPanel()` | Init state + start timers |
| `startDelegationStep(label)` | Relabel active OR activate next pending OR push new |
| `pushPlanStep(label)` | Complete current active, push new active |
| `updatePlanStepDetail(detail)` | Set `detail` (string) or `detailLines` (string[]) on active step |
| `completePlanStep()` | Mark active → completed (no auto-advance) |
| `errorPlanStep()` | Mark active → errored |
| `clearPlanPanel()` | Stop timers, null state, clear widget |
| `renderPlanStatusText()` | Single-line summary with `⚡` + dot progress |

